{
  "stem": "11723.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he was an unmarried man without children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He had a girlfriend, a countess, the Countess Elvira.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they took my father in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he arranged with one of the lieutenants serving under him when he was still active to taking my mother, supposedly as his mistress.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she, of course, was called Irene Kovacs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Everybody was Kovacs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My father was supposed to have been Andrew Kovacs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He was Armin, but I guess they thought that was too Jewish, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now, there was always the fear that someone else is going to-- someone's going to recognize us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So the scheme was that, as I said already, my father would be with his friend, my mother with this lieutenant, and we children would be separated.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We would be placed in a foundling home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And my grandparents, my grandparents Katz, my cousin Peter, and my Aunt Elsa, who Aunt Elsa was my father's younger sister, and her son Peter, and Aunt Roszi was my father's older brother's wife, and Eva, her child, they all went into a place called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "That was like a sanatorium or a place where people recuperate.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Not really a nursing home, but a sanatorium on the Buda side of Pest.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they all had false papers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they paid a huge sum of money in order to be in this place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And when the time came and they took people to the ghetto, my other grandmother, Grandma Gluck, or Gluck, Maria, she was taken to the ghetto, as my mother's mother, with her daughter-in-law and two children-- two grandchildren of hers, two children of the daughter-in-law's, my mother's older brother's wife and two children.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Now, when my mother found out that her mother had been taken to the ghetto, she went ballistic.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "She was hysterical.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
